In the current version of echarts, the highlighted color can only be calculated manually by:
```js
var normalColor = '#0188fb';
var emphasisColor = echarts.color.lift(normalColor, -0.1);
```

This option works.

```js
option = {
    xAxis: { type: 'time' },
    yAxis: { type: 'value' },
    visualMap: {
        type: 'piecewise',
        show: false,
        dimension: 0,
        pieces: [{
            gt: +new Date('2020-04-01T00:00'),
            lte: +new Date('2020-04-01T01:00'),
            color: 'blue'
        }, {
            gt: +new Date('2020-04-01T01:00'),
            lte: +new Date('2020-04-01T04:00'),
            color: 'red'
        }]
    },
    tooltip:{ trigger: "axis" },
    series: [{
        type: 'line',
        data: [
            ['2020-04-01T00:00', 200],
            ['2020-04-01T01:00', 400],
            ['2020-04-01T02:00', 650],
            ['2020-04-01T03:00', 500]
        ]
    }]
};
```

But notice each piece should both contain `lt`/`lte`  and `gt`/`gte`.
(this should be enhanced)
